description.narrative: The National Health Sector Strategic Plan aims to support the Government of Timor-Leste (GoTL) to provide/organise resources to where they are needed most to improve delivery of health services in districts and sub-districts. The expected outcomes include: Ministry of Health (MoH) implementing the 'One Plan, One Budget, One Monitoring &#38;#38; Evaluation Framework'; MoH, working closely with Ministry of Finance, developing stronger financial management and procurement systems that enable DPs to use government systems (and be in a stronger position to receive sector budget support); and MoH working closely with a broad range of partners to improve the delivery of health services, particularly in Community Health Centres, Health Posts, and through regular community outreach visits (SISCas).
